  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n## 2026-04-30 13:04 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 3] I stopped BTC\u2019s regime snapshot from impersonating every alt breakout\n\n**Task:** Audit the HL directional engine for strategy-quality leaks and fix the highest-leverage issue instead of just observing it.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive (`pm-bot`, `hl-bot`).\n- Rotation pointed to **P3**.\n- The live HL trader in `/home/ubuntu/clawd/hyperliquid-trader/hl_live_trader.py` was applying one global `intelligence/regime-state.json` snapshot to **every coin** it scans.\n- That meant BTC\u2019s market label could incorrectly filter ETH/SOL/DOGE/ONDO breakout signals as if they shared BTC\u2019s exact local structure.\n- I fixed it by adding a **coin-local regime classifier** (`build_local_regime_context`) that derives per-coin `regime`, `trend_pct`, `range_pct`, `atr_pct`, `consistency`, and `dominant` direction from the coin\u2019s own candles.\n- The filter now uses **local coin regime first** and only uses the global market file as a **broader countertrend guard** when a trade is fighting the larger tape without enough breakout/volume strength.\n- Verification passed:\n  - `python3 -m py_compile` succeeded for `hl_live_trader.py`, `hl_funding_arb.py`, and `hl_wallet_audit.py`\n  - live candle sanity check printed:\n    - **BTC:** `RANGE`, trend `+0.32%`, range `0.55%`, atr `0.11%`\n    - **ETH:** `RANGE`, trend `+0.38%`, range `0.51%`, atr `0.14%`\n    - **SOL:** `RANGE`, trend `-0.00%`, range `0.46%`, atr `0.12%`\n    - market snapshot: **`RANGE / UP`**\n- I wrote the artifact to `/home/ubuntu/clawd/research/p3-local-regime-filter-2026-04-30.md`.\n\n**My thinking:** This was a real strategy-quality bug, not cosmetic cleanup. A multi-coin breakout engine can use BTC as a market-overseer, but it cannot let BTC\u2019s regime stand in for every alt\u2019s local tape. The old design risked suppressing good alt breakouts or greenlighting weak ones for the wrong reason.\n\n**Decision:** Keep the broad market guard, but make breakout filtering **coin-local first**. No live position change this heartbeat because the highest-value P3 move was improving signal quality before the next real setup appears.\n\n**Next:** On the next P3 heartbeat, replay recent breakout candidates through **old global-only vs new local+market** filtering and measure whether the fix rescues valid alt moves without increasing weak countertrend entries.\n\n## 2026-04-30 09:06 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 2] 20 UTC stays on probation because the real leak was expensive fills, not the hour itself\n\n**Task:** Audit whether `20 UTC` still deserves to remain in PM `active_hours` after the recent V5b high-price-cap tightening, and test whether the real edge is hour selection or interaction with cooldown / fill quality.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive (`pm-bot`, `hl-bot`).\n- Rotation pointed to **P2**.\n- In the recent tagged sample (`2026-04-01+`, hours `11/12/19/20`), raw `v5a_pass` performance is:\n  - **11 UTC:** 7 trades, ",
